ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this class to another student because I felt like I definitely improved my Swahili skills. I would feel fairly comfortable returning to Tanzania and conversing with a native speaker.
Compared to L1-2, L3 of Kiswahili includes more overall work in terms of regular activities, but also bolsters your reading and writing skills a lot.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course has convinced me that I want to continue studying East Africa, specifically Tanzania, and that I want to return to the region to conduct further research. I know that I want to continue studying Swahili no matter what I do after graduation this upcoming May.

While not directly relevant to my thesis or research, this course did help me improve my Swahili, which will prove useful in the future, and helped me better understand African languages in general, others of which I may pursue in the future.
